herited constants via subclass access. It seems I should also add assertions for the active capability and requirement, and check if checkstyle has any issues with static usage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering capability tests**\\n\\nI’m contemplating whether to change to Namespace, but I worry about losing a feature. I could add a test for the capability `uses` directive, which is relevant since the ServiceLoaderNamespace can include it. \\n\\nThere’s mention of CAPABILITY_USES_DIRECTIVE, but I should ensure the `uses` directive is recognized as a public feature. This could be functional and undetected so far. I’ll create a test method to declare used packages with the inherited directive, combining inherited and service constants while avoiding extra helpers. It seems the `uses` directive should be capability-specific.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing service loader issues**\\n\\nI need to address the missing \\\"uses\\\" and \\\"effective\\\" parts related to `serviceLoaderSpecificConstantsDoNotCollideWithGenericNamespaceKeys`. It seems the focus is on ensuring there's collision but not a clear usage. Maybe adding a test would suffice. I'm considering whether I need a \\\"public API with no reflection\\\" and if I should adjust any imports. I don't think new imports are necessary, so it could just be a matter of adding a method in the right place.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Mzd1DqBpnD9j0whKEdi9B2NH|fc_05505d73b317fed90169ef88f162808195937375096718208b", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.osgi/org.osgi.service.serviceloader/1.0.0/src/test/java/org_osgi/org_osgi_service_serviceloader/Org_osgi_service_serviceloaderTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void serviceLoaderRequirementUsesNamespaceAttributeInStandardRequirementDirectives() {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void serviceLoaderCapabilityCanUseInheritedCapabilityDirectives() {\n        Capability capability = serviceLoaderCapability(\n                Map.of(\n                        ServiceLoaderNamespace.CAPABILITY_USES_DIRECTIVE, \"org.example.spi,org.example.model\",\n                        ServiceLoaderNamespace.CAPABILITY_EFFECTIVE_DIRECTIVE, ServiceLoaderNamespace.EFFECTIVE_ACTIVE\n                ),\n                Map.of()\n        );\n\n        assertThat(capability.getDirectives())\n                .containsEntry(ServiceLoaderNamespace.CAPABILITY_USES_DIRECTIVE, \"org.example.spi,org.example.model\")\n                .containsEntry(ServiceLoaderNamespace.CAPABILITY_EFFECTIVE_DIRECTIVE, ServiceLoaderNamespace.EFFECTIVE_ACTIVE);\n        assertThat(capability.getAttributes())\n                .containsOnly(Map.entry(ServiceLoaderNamespace.SERVICELOADER_NAMESPACE, SERVICE_TYPE));\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void serviceLoaderRequirementUsesNamespaceAttributeInStandardRequirementDirectives() {\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2146, "output": 878, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22992, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777305823765, "responseId": "resp_05505d73b317fed90169ef88e08168819592501725bd45ba19"}}
